--- Part 3: n=7 chi_rel analysis ---
  ... 10 beta_3=1 found
  ... 20 beta_3=1 found
  ... 30 beta_3=1 found
  ... 40 beta_3=1 found

  n=7 chi_rel for BAD vertices (b3_Tv=1): {0: 34}
  n=7 chi_rel for GOOD vertices (b3_Tv=0): {-1: 316}

--- Part 4: Key observation ---
  From LES: sum_p (-1)^p H_p^rel = chi_rel
  If H_0^rel = 1, H_1^rel = 0, H_2^rel = 0 (from beta_2=0 and LES),
  then: H_3^rel - H_4^rel + H_5^rel - ... = chi_rel - 1
  For beta_3=1, H_3^rel in {0,1}:
    If H_3^rel = 1: -H_4^rel + H_5^rel - ... = chi_rel - 2
    If H_3^rel = 0: -H_4^rel + H_5^rel - ... = chi_rel - 1

  H_0(T,T\v) should be 1 (T connected, T\v connected, one component difference)
  H_1(T,T\v) and H_2(T,T\v) from LES:
    ... H_1(T) = 0 (most T, since beta_3=1 => beta_1=0 by seesaw)
    ... H_1(T\v) = 0 (mostly, since beta_3_Tv >= 0)
    LES: H_1(T\v) -> H_1(T) -> H_1(T,T\v) -> H_0(T\v) -> H_0(T)
    H_0(T\v) = 1, H_0(T) = 1 => connecting map H_1(T,T\v) -> H_0(T\v)

DONE.
